values:
Hello,

Long time no update. >_>;

&lt;bitch&gt;
I've officially dubbed this week the Week of Hell. I have two (largish) group assignments due on Friday, so from Saturday evening onwards I've been spending 6pm -> 12pm at uni doing project work (on top of the usual 9-5), culminating in a planned all-nighter on Thursday to get it all finished off (I wish). It also means I have to do my database assignment during lunchbreak at work. *Whinge/Bitch/Moan*

(To those that see me around the place in real life: I'm going to be a wibbling mess by the time Friday rolls around, please forgive me if I'm slightly incoherent. *Mumbles*)
&lt;/bitch&gt;

(Umm, the above means I'm most probably out of Rocky this week. I'll SMS Justin later on today. :[ )

Right, cathartic whining session over. Thank you for being a lovely audience (and for not yawning too much).


(Just as an aside, does anyone know how to make thin, hard foam hold its shape when it's bent? I have to shape a bunch of foam strips, and I've no idea how to keep them bent in a curve. :S )

*Phew*

<a href="http://insanitymanga.net/forums">InsanityManga.net's Forums</a> membership has just been halved, thanks to <a href="http://www.phpbbhacks.com/download/1692">this</a> handy Admin Panel mod for phpBB. So many damn f*ckin' spammer accounts ("got PH3NTERMIINE?!!!1").

Le sigh.

Anyway, in more productive (and less make-work) news, I've finally committed a working version of the new site following a code run that lasted until 5am. O_O;

Note to self, never do this again (this had me stuck for half an hour at least - put two of these in a row, and it prints out an infinite loop of '0's):
<pre>foreach ($content['main'] as $title => $content) {
    echo $title; // print stuff out
}</pre>
Redeclaring the array you're looping through isn't smart. This also proves that foreach() doesn't get the array by reference. -_-;

In any case, time to get on with filling out that damn driver's logbook so I can pass my P's Test. And reports. And uploading photos. And catching up on STF posting. And cleaning the house. (Gah!)

- Cabbage
